  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    CalledFromGeneratedCode
    Use this annotation to signal that a method that would otherwise appear unused is actually called from generated code.
    MarkerInterface
    This annotation signals that an interface is only used for marking types, and that the interface should not define any methods.
    VisibleForTesting
    Annotation to indicate that program element exists, or has visibility wider than necessary, only for testing purposes.
